nger, bullying, shame\n|\nWriting has nothing to do with meaning. It has to do with landsurveying and cartography, including the mapping of countries yet to come.\n\n- Gilles\n|\nGrateful people are happy people. The more things you are grateful for, the happier you will be.\n\n- Roy\n|\nTell me, what is it you plan to do with your one wild and precious life?\n\n- Mary\n|\nWithout trust in the possibilities for your life, where would you be? Where would any of us be? Our hopes for the future give us momentum.\n\n- Nick Vujicic, Life Without Limits\n|\nWhen you feel life at crossroads,you need higher perspective view.\n\n- Toba Beta, My Ancestor Was an Ancient Astronaut\n|\nShe loved the smell of books, the feel of books, the look of them on the shelf.\n\n- Barbara Michaels, Houses of Stone\n|\nIn worthy teaching, all things are related.\n\n- Confucius, The Analects\n|\nNever compare your love story to those you watch in movies. They're written by scriptwriters, yours is written by God.\n\n- Efren\n|\nFaith, the least exclusive club on Earth, has the craftiest doorman.\n\n- David\n|\nNext to the day when I was almost shot by that arrow, the worst day of my life was when I was almost eaten.\n\n- Jennifer Frick-Ruppert, Spirit Quest\n|\nIf experience is the best teacher, there's nothing that comes close to the experience of life.\n\n- Michael A. Singer, The Untethered Soul: The Journey Beyond Yourself\n|\nPrivate life, book life, took place where words met imagination without passing through the world.\n\n- Annie Dillard, An American Childhood\n|\nI believe in Christianity as I believe that the sun has risen: not only because I see it, but because by it I see everything else.\n\n- C.S.\n|\nYour external world is a mirror of your internal world, and if you can discipline yourself to change your thoughts, your external world will change.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nHonestly, I hate when in books, the guys changes the girl's life. Like, no. The girl needs to change her own life.\n\n- Sasha\n|\nTo most Christians, the Bible is like a software license. Nobody actually reads it. They just scroll to the bottom and click 'I agree'.\n\n- Bill\n|\nGod, listen to the absurdity within us and raise us from the illusion!\n\n- Sorin Cerin, Wisdom Collection: The Book of Wisdom\n|\nWords can mean nothing, or be daggers in someone's heart. Choose them wisely.\n\n- Christian\n|\nYour rebel soul shines like a diamond pulled from dust: bright, clear and flawless.\n\n- Jay\n|\nThe world is already full of critics; to stand out, be an encourager.\n\n- Matshona\n|\n...and there you have it, another body on the floor surrounded by things that don't mean much to anyone except to the one who can't take any of them along.\n\n- Mark Z. Danielewski, House of Leaves\n|\nYou want to give him the book of his own life, the book that will locate him, parent him, arm him for the changes.\n\n- Michael Cunningham, The Hours\n|\nIf you want to build a ship, don’t drum up the men to gather wood, divide the work, and give orders. Instead, teach them to yearn for the vast and endless sea.\n\n- Antoine\n|\nIntelligence does not always define wisdom, but adaptability to change does.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI think I exist, therefore I exist. I think.\n\n- David Gerrold, The Man Who Folded Himself\n|\nLove is like lightening; it can strike anyone, anywhere, and at any time.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nThe Moving Finger writes; and, having writ,Moves on: nor all thy Piety nor WitShall lure it back to cancel half a Line,Nor all thy Tears wash out a Word of it.\n\n- Omar\n|\nLearn from your past and be better because of your past, but don't cry about your past. Life is full of pain. Let the pain sharpen you, but don't hold on to it. Don't be bitter.\n\n- Trevor Noah, Born A Crime: Stories from a South African Childhood\n|\nEverybody does have a book in them, but in most cases that's where it should stay.\n\n- Christopher\n|\nThe more you learn, the more you want to learn.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think 